The "windows" part of the cookbook's name is simply to distinguish it from the versions of this project for [Red Hat Enterprise Linux](/modules/create-a-web-app-cookbook/) and [Ubuntu](/modules/create-a-web-app-cookbook/ubuntu/). We break many of the tutorials into these categories to help you focus on the platform you care about most. In practice, you could write a single cookbook that runs on multiple platforms. In that case, you might name the cookbook simply `awesome_customers`.

